    <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545"> 
      <head altrender="organization" id="a2">ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY </head> 
      <p>Barbara Booker was an avid runner, camper, hiker, triathlete and cross
        country skier and the first woman president of the Finger Lakes Runners Club.
        Under her direction the club began to focus on open competition and women's
        running in road races and marathons.</p> 
    </bioghist> 
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520"> 
      <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head> 
      <p>Includes records pertaining to various track and cross-country skiing
        races and events, including meet results, workout schedules and
        memorabilia.</p> 
    </scopecontent> 
